news.title: Protean eGov Technologies leases 68,021 sq ft office space in Mumbai
news.para: Colliers India, a real estate services firm, helped transacted the deal. The company's design services team will also design the project.

news.title: West Bengal forms panel to check building complaints outside Kolkata civic body
news.para: The committee will also look into minor deviations from the sanctioned plan or execution of any minor work in contravention of any sanctioned plan under the provisions of the West Bengal Municipal (Building) Rules, 2007.

news.title: Hubballi Dharwad civic body to pioneer Karnataka's first 3D GIS survey
news.para: Hubballi-Dharwad Municipal Corporation (HDMC) is set to become the state's pioneer in conducting a comprehensive 3D GIS survey, with plans to begin in the first week of March.

news.title: Nagpur civic body yet to recover Rs 224 crore in property tax dues
news.para: The NMC has intensified its recovery drive by issuing warrants and attaching properties to meet its target. But, a significant amount remains unpaid.

news.title: Kerala government likely to approve Thiruvananthapuram metro rail project soon
news.para: Once the chief minister approves the alignment, it will be tabled for cabinet approval, which is expected by the end of this month.

news.title: Commission asks Jodhpur development body to refund excess amount of plot to consumer
news.para: Additionally, charging a higher price from the consumer for an alternative plot is an unfair trade practice. The commission has also ordered the refund of the excess amount charged from the consumer.

news.title: SC stays HC's contempt order on South Mumbai flats' 'illegal' merger
news.para: Sukhshanti CHSL had complained to BMC that its members, Mahimtura and Gangji, owners of a flat on the ground floor, amalgamated an adjoining flat owned by a deceased member.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body approved 2,858 building plans in eight years without authority: RTI reply
news.para: According to regulations, the authority for plan approvals was transferred to the Bhubaneswar Municipal Corporation (BMC) in 2015 within the civic body's jurisdiction, yet BDA persisted in issuing approvals, violating established protocols.

news.title: Almost all of 200-acre Silicon Valley allotted to IT firms: West Bengal CM
news.para: "We initially thought of setting up Silicon Valley on 100 acres. We revised the size and made provisions for 200 acres. Almost the entire land has been allocated to companies," Banerjee said after the Budget was tabled.

news.title: Demand for mixed-use developments rises in Pune
news.para: Mixed-use projects incorporate multiple functionalities, such as residential housing, retail hubs and recreational facilities, into one community.

news.title: Developer, RWAs served notice for flouting building code in Gurugram
news.para: The notice, issued under Section 10(2) of the Haryana Development and Regulations of Urban Areas Act, 1975, highlights violations of approved building plans and warns of legal action if corrective measures are not taken immediately.

news.title: Only 88 of 80,000 lifts registered, Noida to hold camps for societies
news.para: Atul Kumar, ADM (finance/revenue), said that of the registered lifts, 68 were in residential highrises, while commercial and industrial establishments accounted for the remaining ones.

news.title: Noida: Flats stuck for years, buyers plan to share Ajnara’s dues to finish project
news.para: Ajnara Realtech Ltd and homebuyers of the realtor's Le Garden project in Sector 16 have submitted a joint proposal — the realtor has agreed to pay Rs 12 crore upfront, of which Rs 5 crore is to be footed by homebuyers — to the Authority under a legacy stalled real estate policy.

news.title: Maharashtra's registration department achieves 85% of revenue target in February
news.para: Data shows 23.72 lakh documents were registered across Maharashtra till Feb 10, fetching Rs46,493.75 crore in revenue.

news.title: Prestige Group may raise Rs 1,000 crore to refinance costly debt
news.para: The secured debt facility, with a three-year tenor maturing in January 2028, will be raised at Bamboo Hotel and Global Centre (Delhi). (BHGCPL) a joint venture between Prestige Group and DB Realty, which is developing a large scale mixed-use project in New Delhi's Aerocity.

news.title: United Kingdom's PM vows 'new towns' to alleviate housing crunch
news.para: The goverment has vowed to build 1.5 million houses by 2029, including through the "next generation" of new towns, which could host 10,000 homes each.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh prepares plan to develop startup-cum-IT park in Indore on PPP model
news.para: "The board of directors of Indore Development Authority has passed a resolution to build a startup-cum-IT park on the Super Corridor on PPP model. The plan will be sent to the state government for final approval," Indore Division Commissioner (Revenue) Deepak Singh told reporters.

news.title: MSRTC to develop 3,360-acre land bank on fast-track mode: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Maharashtra's transport minister Pratap Sarnaik said there is a need to develop the "strategically located" lands, and urged real estate developers to come forward to develop commercial or residential premises on it, as per the statement.

news.title: SC directs Sahara, SEBI to hold meet over group's Versova land
news.para: ​A bench of Chief Justice Sanjiv Khanna and Justices M M Sundresh and Bela M Trivedi issued notices to the Ministry of Environment and Forests and Maharashtra's chief secretary and sought their responses on the status of Versova plot and clarify whether it was a forest land.

news.title: China considers plan to help Vanke repay $6.8 billion debt
news.para: The proposal involves regulators allocating 20 billion yuan in special local government bonds to buy unsold properties and vacant land from Vanke, the report on Wednesday said, citing people familiar with the matter.
